    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Application
    Entry point of the SVG Editor application.
    AttributeGetter
    Utility class for extracting attribute values and mapping color strings.
    Circle
    Represents a circle shape with center coordinates, radius, and fill color.
    Clear
    Command to clear all shapes from the ShapeList.
    Colours
    Enum representing available colors.
    CommandException
    Exception thrown when a command encounters an error.
    Create
    Command to create a new shape and add it to the ShapeList.
    Erase
    Command to erase a shape from the ShapeList by its index.
    Executable
    Represents a command or action that can be executed with arguments.
    Executer
    Manages and provides command executables based on command strings.
    FileException
    Exception thrown when a file-related error occurs.
    FileSaver
    Utility class for saving SVG files.
    Help
    Command to display a list of all available commands and their usage.
    Line
    Represents a line shape with start and end coordinates, stroke color, and stroke width.
    Open
    Command to open and read shapes from an SVG file.
    Print
    Command to print information about all shapes currently stored in the ShapeList.
    Program
    Main program loop for the SVG Editor command-line interface.
    Rectangle
    Represents a rectangle shape with position, size, and fill color.
    Save
    Command to save the current shapes to the opened file.
    SaveAs
    Command to save the current shapes to a new file with a specified name.
    Shape
    Represents a geometric shape with common operations.
    ShapeFactory
    Factory class responsible for creating shape instances dynamically.
    ShapeList
    Singleton class that manages the list of shapes and the current file name.
    Translate
    Command to translate shapes by given x and y offsets.
    Within
    Command to list shapes within a specified rectangular area.
